\\"failed to glob old transcript files: %v\\\", err)\\n  4544→+\\t}\\n  4545→+\\tif len(oldTranscriptFiles) > 0 {\\n  4546→+\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"old Claude project dir should not have transcript files after resume, but found %d\\\", len(oldTranscriptFiles))\\n  4547→+\\t}\\n  4548→+\\n  4549→+\\t// Verify output contains session info\\n  4550→+\\tif !strings.Contains(output, \\\"Session:\\\") {\\n  4551→+\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"output should contain 'Session:', got: %s\\\", output)\\n  4552→+\\t}\\n  4553→+}\\n  4554→diff --git a/e2e/README.md b/e2e/README.md\\n  4555→new file mode 100644\\n  4556→index 000000000..746a55dde\\n  4557→--- /dev/null\\n  4558→+++ b/e2e/README.md\\n  4559→@@ -0,0 +1,85 @@\\n  4560→+# E2E Tests\\n  4561→+\\n  4562→+End-to-end tests for the `entire` CLI against real agents (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode).\\n  4563→+\\n  4564→+## Commands\\n  4565→+\\n  4566→+```bash\\n  4567→+mise run test:e2e TestFoo              # run filtered (or omit filter for all agents)\\n  4568→+mise run test:e2e:claude TestFoo       # Claude Code only\\n  4569→+mise run test:e2e:gemini TestFoo       # Gemini CLI only (sequential, avoids rate limits)\\n  4570→+mise run test:e2e:opencode TestFoo     # OpenCode only\\n  4571→+go build ./...                         # compile check (no agent CLI needed)\\n  4572→+```\\n  4573→+\\n  4574→+**Do NOT run E2E tests proactively.** They make real API calls that consume tokens and cost money. Only run when explicitly asked.\\n  4575→+\\n  4576→+## Structure\\n  4577→+\\n  4578→+```\\n  4579→+e2e/\\n  4580→+├── agents/       # Agent abstraction (Agent interface, tmux sessions, concurrency gates)\\n  4581→+├── bootstrap/    # CI pre-test setup (auth config, warmup)\\n  4582→+├── entire/       # `entire` CLI wrapper (enable, rewind, etc.)\\n  4583→+├── exploratory/  # Experimental tests, not run by CI\\n  4584→+├── tests/        # Blessed test files (run by CI)\\n  4585→+└── testutil/     # Repo setup, assertions, artifact capture\\n  4586→+```\\n  4587→+\\n  4588→+## Key Patterns\\n  4589→+\\n  4590→+- Every test uses `testutil.ForEachAgent` which runs it per registered agent with repo setup, concurrency gating, and timeout scaling.\\n  4591→+- All operations go through `RepoState` (`s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`) so they're logged to `console.log`.\\n  4592→+- Use the `entire` package for CLI interactions, not raw `exec.Command`.\\n  4593→+- Skip tests pending CLI fixes with `t.Skip(\\\"ENT-XXX: reason\\\")`.\\n  4594→+\\n  4595→+## Adding a New Agent\\n  4596→+\\n  4597→+1. Create `agents/<name>.go` implementing the `Agent` interface.\\n  4598→+2. Register it in `init()` with `Register(&YourAgent{})`.\\n  4599→+3. Add a `Bootstrap()` method for any CI-specific setup (auth config, warmup).\\n  4600→+4. Add a `RegisterGate(\\\"<name>\\\", N)` call if concurrency needs limiting.\\n  4601→+5. Add a `test:e2e:<name>` task in `mise.toml`.\\n  4602→+6. Add the agent to `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` matrix and `e2e-isolated.yml` options.\\n  4603→+\\n  4604→+## Environment Variables\\n  4605→+\\n  4606→+| Variable | Description | Default |\\n  4607→+|----------|-------------|---------|\\n  4608→+| `E2E_AGENT` | Agent to test (`claude-code`, `gemini-cli`, `opencode`) | all registered |\\n  4609→+| `E2E_TIMEOUT` | Timeout per prompt | `2m` |\\n  4610→+| `E2E_KEEP_REPOS` | Set to `1` to preserve temp repos after test | unset |\\n  4611→+| `E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR` | Override artifact output directory | `e2e/artifacts/<timestamp>` |\\n  4612→+| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Required for Claude Code | — |\\n  4613→+| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | Required for Gemini CLI | — |\\n  4614→+\\n  4615→+## Debugging Failures\\n  4616→+\\n  4617→+Artifacts are captured to `e2e/artifacts/` on every run (git-log, git-tree, console.log, checkpoint metadata, entire logs). Set `E2E_KEEP_REPOS=1` to preserve the temp repo — a symlink appears in the artifact dir pointing to it.\\n  4618→+\\n  4619→+Use the `debug-e2e` skill (`.claude/skills/debug-e2e/`) for a structured workflow when investigating failures.\\n  4620→+\\n  4621→+### Reading artifacts\\n  4622→+\\n  4623→+- `console.log` — full operation transcript including agent stdout/stderr\\n  4624→+- `git-log.txt` — commit history at time of failure\\n  4625→+- `git-tree.txt` — working tree state\\n  4626→+- `entire-logs/` — internal CLI logs\\n  4627→+\\n  4628→+### Fixing flaky tests\\n  4629→+\\n  4630→+When a test passes on retry but failed once, the problem is usually agent non-determinism, not a CLI bug. Common patterns:\\n  4631→+\\n  4632→+- **Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting**: The model output contains \\\"Does this look right?\\\" or \\\"Should I proceed?\\\". Fix: append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation, just make the change.\\\" to the prompt.\\n  4633→+- **Agent wrote to wrong path or created extra files**: Fix: be more explicit about exact file paths and what _not_ to do.\\n  4634→+- **Agent committed when it shouldn't have**: Fix: add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to the prompt.\\n  4635→+- **Checkpoint wait timeout**: `WaitForCheckpoint` or `WaitForCheckpointAdvanceFrom` exceeded deadline. Fix: increase the timeout argument.\\n  4636→+\\n  4637→+To diagnose: read `console.log` in the failing test's artifact directory. Compare what the agent actually did vs what the test expected.\\n  4638→+\\n  4639→+## CI Workflows\\n  4640→+\\n  4641→+- **`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`** — Runs full suite on push to main. Matrix: `[claude, opencode, gemini]`.\\n  4642→+- **`.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml`** — Manual dispatch for debugging a single test. Inputs: agent + test name filter.\\n  4643→+\\n  4644→+Both workflows run `go run ./e2e/bootstrap` before tests to handle agent-specific CI setup (auth config, warmup).\\n  4645→diff --git a/e2e/agents/agent.go b/e2e/agents/agent.go\\n  4646→new file mode 100644\\n  4647→index 000000000..8799c0ac2\\n  4648→--- /dev/null\\n  4649→+++ b/e2e/agents/agent.go\\n  4650→@@ -0,0 +1,94 @@\\n  4651→+package agents\\n  4652→+\\n  4653→+import (\\n  4654→+\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n  4655→+\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n  4656→+)\\n  4657→+\\n  4658→+type Output struct {\\n  4659→+\\tCommand  string\\n  4660→+\\tStdout   string\\n  4661→+\\tStderr   string\\n  4662→+\\tExitCode int\\n  4663→+}\\n  4664→+\\n  4665→+type Option func(*runConfig)\\n  4666→+type runConfig struct {\\n  4667→+\\tModel          string\\n  4668→+\\tPermissionMode string\\n  4669→+}\\n  4670→+\\n  4671→+func WithModel(model string) Option {\\n  4672→+\\treturn func(c *runConfig) { c.Model = model }\\n  4673→+}\\n  4674→+\\n  4675→+func WithPermissionMode(mode string) Option {\\n  4676→+\\treturn func(c *runConfig) { c.PermissionMode = mode }\\n  4677→+}\\n  4678→+\\n  4679→+type Agent interface {\\n  4680→+\\tName() string\\n  4681→+\\t// Binary returns the CLI binary name (e.g. \\\"claude\\\", \\\"gemini\\\").\\n  4682→+\\tBinary() string\\n  4683→+\\tEntireAgent() string\\n  4684→+\\tPromptPattern() string\\n  4685→+\\t// TimeoutMultiplier returns a factor applied to per-test timeouts.\\n  4686→+\\t// Slower agents (e.g. Gemini) return values > 1.\\n  4687→+\\tTimeoutMultiplier() float64\\n  4688→+\\tRunPrompt(ctx context.Context, dir string, prompt string, opts ...Option) (Output, error)\\n  4689→+\\tStartSession(ctx context.Context, dir string) (Session, error)\\n  4690→+\\t// Bootstrap performs one-time CI setup (auth config, warmup, etc.).\\n  4691→+\\t// Called before any tests run. Implementations should be idempotent.\\n  4692→+\\tBootstrap() error\\n  4693→+\\t// IsTransientError returns true if the error from RunPrompt looks like\\n  4694→+\\t// a transient API failure (e.g. 500, rate limit, network error) that\\n  4695→+\\t// is worth retrying.\\n  4696→+\\tIsTransientError(out Output, err error) bool\\n  4697→+}\\n  4698→+\\n  4699→+type Session interface {\\n  4700→+\\tSend(input string) error\\n  4701→+\\tWaitFor(pattern string, timeout time.Duration) (string, error)\\n  4702→+\\tCapture() string\\n  4703→+\\tClose() error\\n  4704→+}\\n  4705→+\\n  4706→+var registry []Agent\\n  4707→+var gates = map[string]chan struct{}{}\\n  4708→+\\n  4709→+func Register(a Agent) {\\n  4710→+\\tregistry = append(registry, a)\\n  4711→+}\\n  4712→+\\n  4713→+// RegisterGate sets a concurrency limit for an agent's tests.\\n  4714→+// Tests call AcquireSlot/ReleaseSlot to respect this limit.\\n  4715→+func RegisterGate(name string, max int) {\\n  4716→+\\tgates[name] = make(chan struct{}, max)\\n  4717→+}\\n  4718→+\\n  4719→+// AcquireSlot blocks until a test slot is available for the agent or the\\n  4720→+// context is cancelled. Returns a non-nil error if the context expires\\n  4721→+// before a slot opens.\\n  4722→+func AcquireSlot(ctx context.Context, a Agent) error {\\n  4723→+\\tg, ok := gates[a.Name()]\\n  4724→+\\tif !ok {\\n  4725→+\\t\\treturn nil\\n  4726→+\\t}\\n  4727→+\\tselect {\\n  4728→+\\tcase g <- struct{}{}:\\n  4729→+\\t\\treturn nil\\n  4730→+\\tcase <-ctx.Done():\\n  4731→+\\t\\treturn ctx.Err()\\n  4732→+\\t}\\n  4733→+}\\n  4734→+\\n  4735→+// ReleaseSlot frees a test slot for the agent.\\n  4736→+func ReleaseSlot(a Agent) {\\n  4737→+\\tif g, ok := gates[a.Name()]; ok {\\n  4738→+\\t\\t<-g\\n  4739→+\\t}\\n  4740→+}\\n  4741→+\\n  4742→+func All() []Agent {\\n  4743→+\\treturn registry\\n  4744→+}\\n  4745→diff --git a/e2e/agents/claude.go b/e2e/agents/claude.go\\n  4746→new file mode 100644\\n  4747→index 000000000..34fb21d88\\n  4748→--- /dev/null\\n  4749→+++ b/e2e/agents/claude.go\\n  4750→@@ -0,0 +1,231 @@\\n  4751→+package agents\\n  4752→+\\n  4753→+import (\\n  4754→+\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n  4755→+\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n  4756→+\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n  4757→+\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n  4758→+\\t\\\"os/exec\\\"\\n  4759→+\\t\\\"path/filepath\\\"\\n  4760→+\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n  4761→+\\t\\\"syscall\\\"\\n  4762→+\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n  4763→+)\\n  4764→+\\n  4765→+// isolatedConfigDir creates a temp directory that mirrors ~/.claude via\\n  4766→+// symlinks but omits CLAUDE.md and skills/ so that test runs don't inherit\\n  4767→+// the operator's personal instructions or custom skills.\\n  4768→+func isolatedConfigDir() (string, error) {\\n  4769→+\\thome, err := os.UserHomeDir()\\n  4770→+\\tif err != nil {\\n  4771→+\\t\\treturn \\\"\\\", fmt.Errorf(\\\"get home dir: %w\\\", err)\\n  4772→+\\t}\\n  4773→+\\tsrc := filepath.Join(home, \\\".claude\\\")\\n  4774→+\\n  4775→+\\tdst, err := os.MkdirTemp(\\\"\\\", \\\"claude-config-*\\\")\\n  4776→+\\tif err != nil {\\n  4777→+\\t\\treturn \\\"\\\", err\\n  4778→+\\t}\\n  4779→+\\n  4780→+\\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(src)\\n  4781→+\\tif err != nil {\\n  4782→+\\t\\treturn dst, fmt.Errorf(\\\"read %s: %w\\\", src, err)\\n  4783→+\\t}\\n  4784→+\\n  4785→+\\tskip := map[string]bool{\\\"CLAUDE.md\\\": true, \\\"skills\\\": true}\\n  4786→+\\tfor _, e := range entries {\\n  4787→+\\t\\tif skip[e.Name()] {\\n  4788→+\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n  4789→+\\t\\t}\\n  4790→+\\t\\t_ = os.Symlink(filepath.Join(src, e.Name()), filepath.Join(dst, e.Name()))\\n  4791→+\\t}\\n  4792→+\\treturn dst, nil\\n  4793→+}\\n  4794→+\\n  4795→+// cleanEnv returns os.Environ() with CLAUDECODE removed so that\\n  4796→+// Claude Code doesn't refuse to start inside this test runner.\\n  4797→+func cleanEnv() []string {\\n  4798→+\\tvar env []string\\n  4799→+\\tfor _, e := range os.Environ() {\\n  4800→+\\t\\tif !strings.HasPrefix(e, \\\"CLAUDECODE=\\\") {\\n  4801→+\\t\\t\\tenv = append(env, e)\\n  4802→+\\t\\t}\\n  4803→+\\t}\\n  4804→+\\treturn env\\n  4805→+}\\n  4806→+\\n  4807→+func init() {\\n  4808→+\\tif env := os.Getenv(\\\"E2E_AGENT\\\"); env != \\\"\\\" && env != \\\"claude-code\\\" {\\n  4809→+\\t\\treturn\\n  4810→+\\t}\\n  4811→+\\tRegister(&Claude{})\\n  4812→+}\\n  4813→+\\n  4814→+type Claude struct{}\\n  4815→+\\n  4816→+func (c *Claude) Name() string               { return \\\"claude-code\\\" }\\n  4817→+func (c *Claude) Binary() string             { return \\\"claude\\\" }\\n  4818→+func (c *Claud